The study of this chapter will enable you to: 1. Discuss the roles and responsibilities of various key agencies in response to a biological event. 2. Discuss the need for command and coordination systems in the event of a biological attack. 3. Describe the importance of the National Incident Management System and the Incident Command System. 4. Discuss the roles of key federal agencies and officials when it comes to response to a biological event at the local level. Discuss life safety issues for responders attending to the scene of a biological event. 6. Discuss considerations and describe methods for biosampling. 7. Describe outbreak containment measures used by public health agencies. 